<subSubSection box="[199,1262,1771,1797]" pageId="2" pageNumber="578" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,654,1797]" box="[199,1262,1771,1797]" pageId="2" pageNumber="578">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1771,1797]" pageId="2" pageNumber="578">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species name is derived from a Korean term, 
<taxonomicName box="[905,985,1771,1797]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Spiniola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hanaro">
<emphasis box="[905,985,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="578">hanaro</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, meaning “all together”.
</paragraph>
